# Frontend Quality Rules

## Astro patterns

- Use `getCollection()` and content schemas (Zod) in `src/content/config.ts` for projects, experience, and awards.
- Pass collection data as props; do not duplicate content in page files.
- MDX: shared prose layout for case studies (Phase 2+).
- Images: explicit dimensions to prevent CLS when added.

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` via `astro/tsconfigs/strict`. No `any` without comment.

## React islands

- Islands live in `src/components/islands/`.
- Maximum island scope: single interactive widget.
- Pass serializable props only. No global state libraries in MVP.
- Do not create React components unless interactivity is required.

## Performance budget

- Homepage JS gzipped target: **< 100KB** (excluding analytics).
- Fonts: max 2 families + mono; `font-display: swap`.
- No third-party scripts on critical path without approval.

## Code style

- Match existing file conventions when editing.
- Prefer small, focused components over monolithic page files.
- Delete unused code and imports in files you touch.

## Before merge

- Run `npm run build`, `npm run check`, and `npm run lint`.
